{
  "texts": [
    "This analysis caters to the geoscience community, and thus avoids a detailed exploration of DL-based techniques.",
    "Similarly, a survey by De Lima et al. (2019) provides insightful analysis of fossil classification via CNNs.",
    "This survey solely focuses on CNNs, and so does not cover a broader spectrum of DL architectures, such as transformers and generative models.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, our survey is the first to analyze DL-based fossil image analysis by stratifying them using classification/segmentation tasks and the type of fossil.",
    "Our review serves as a guide for researchers at the intersection of computer science and paleontology, offering the tools and insights needed to apply AI computational methods to advance imaging in paleontological research."
  ]
}